│ triggered because getEntryCost() accesses E->getOperand(0) for a TreeEntry that has no │
│ operands initialized (Operands.size() == 0). Assertions should be treated as correct;  │
│ hence the error indicates earlier logic allowed an entry without operands to be        │
│ queried for operands.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\nThe debug log shows SLP built        │
│ multiple bundles and then calculates costs. The crash occurs after 'Calculated costs   │
│ for Tree: 19' for a casts bundle. In getEntryCost(), a lambda GetCastContextHint is    │
│ defined at around line 9574 which unconditionally calls                                │
│ getSameOpcode(E->getOperand(0), *TLI) when there is no TreeEntry for the provided      │
│ value. If E has no operands (possible for gather or certain constructed nodes), this   │
│ triggers the assertion.\nThe stack frame points to getOperand() and getEntryCost()     │
│ around line 9607, consistent with the lambda definition and usage.\n\n3. Root Cause    │
│ Analysis:\nThe lambda GetCastContextHint assumes all TreeEntries have operands and     │
│ blindly accesses E->getOperand(0). However, gather nodes and some specialized entries  │
│ (e.g., non-standard constructed nodes) may have empty Operands. Even for non-gather    │
│ entries, there are sequences (like combined nodes or entries with alternate opcodes)   │
│ where Operands might not be set at the time of cost computation (e.g., due to being    │
│ formed as part of a scheduling decision without recursive operand building yet).       │
│ Therefore, getEntryCost must guard against empty operands when deriving source         │
│ instruction state for cast context hints. Failing to do so results in the 'Off bounds' │
│ assertion.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\n- Edit in                                     │
│ llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp near the definition of                 │
│ GetCastContextHint in BoUpSLP::getEntryCost(). Add a defensive check for               │
│ E->getNumOperands() before calling E->getOperand(0). If there are no operands, return  │
│ a neutral hint (None) without querying operands.\n\nEdit content (conceptual):\nAt     │
│ lines ~9570-9580, change the lambda to:\n\nauto GetCastContextHint = [&](Value *V) {\n │
│ if (const TreeEntry *OpTE = getTreeEntry(V))\n    return getCastContextHint(*OpTE);\n  │
│ // Guard: some entries may not have operands initialized yet.\n  if                    │
│ (E->getNumOperands() == 0)\n    return TTI::CastContextHint::None;\n                   │
│ InstructionsState SrcState = getSameOpcode(E->getOperand(0), *TLI);\n  if              │
│ (SrcState.getOpcode() == Instruction::Load && !SrcState.isAltShuffle())\n    return    │
│ TTI::CastContextHint::GatherScatter;\n  return TTI::CastContextHint::None;\n};\n\nThis │
│ preserves existing behavior when operands are present, and avoids the assertion by     │
│ returning a safe default when they are not.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe fix adds a guard to │
│ avoid accessing non-existent operands when computing cast context hints during cost    │
│ modeling. This prevents the assertion failure in TreeEntry::getOperand() without       │
│ altering vectorization decisions in cases where operand information is unavailable; we │
│ default to 'None' cast context. Expected effect: the reproducer no longer crashes      │
│ under slp-vectorizer, and cost computation proceeds correctly."})                      │
